00:38:21,465 --> 00:38:25,128
对K不知为何 我就是无法说谎
I don't know... Yeah, for some reason I don't know how.

505
00:38:26,070 --> 00:38:29,437
我告诉他我和男生 同住一间房间，他已经很生气了
He was mad enough when I told him I was staying in a hotel room with a guy.

506
00:38:29,607 --> 00:38:31,165
-还不只如此 -是啊K
- That was one thing. - Yeah, yeah.

507
00:38:31,342 --> 00:38:33,333
当我说和我过夜的男生
When I told him I was staying in a hotel...

508
00:38:33,511 --> 00:38:39,973
我有点喜欢 他就完全失控了
...with a guy that I maybe sort of liked, he lost it.

509
00:38:43,254 --> 00:38:46,246
等等K你说什么？
Wait. Wait, what?

510
00:38:46,424 --> 00:38:48,358
你不介意吧？
Is that okay?

511
00:39:02,606 --> 00:39:05,131
至少让我们载你到镇上
At least let us take you into town.

512
00:39:06,077 --> 00:39:10,707
不用，要是被人看见 跟你们一起，我就麻烦大了
No. If I'm seen with you it's a lot of trouble for me.

513
00:39:10,881 --> 00:39:12,746
我可以用走的 只有一里远
I can walk. It's only a mile.

514
00:39:12,917 --> 00:39:15,351
多亏你的帮忙 我们才能逃到这里
We never would've made it this far without you.

515
00:39:15,886 --> 00:39:19,686
现在你们要离开我 跨越边境了
But now you're crossing the border without me.

516
00:39:20,157 --> 00:39:21,920
你不能去我们要去的地方
You can't go where we're going.

517
00:39:22,626 --> 00:39:24,116
那种生活不适合你
It's not a life for you.

518
00:39:28,265 --> 00:39:30,165
那么就这样了
Then that's it, then.

519
00:39:31,535 --> 00:39:33,526
我们永别了
It's over for good.

520
00:39:34,305 --> 00:39:35,294
谢谢你
Thank you.

521
00:39:37,775 --> 00:39:39,436
你要小心点
Be safe.

522
00:39:45,950 --> 00:39:47,440
祝你们好运
Good luck.

523
00:39:54,525 --> 00:39:56,993
我爱过你，麦可
I loved you, Michael.

524
00:39:57,495 --> 00:40:00,555
我以为你也会爱我 但是你只是在利用我
And I thought I was gonna get that back, but you just used me.

525
00:40:01,031 --> 00:40:03,795
-不是这样的 -你不该这么对我
- That's not true. - I deserve more than this.

526
00:40:04,301 --> 00:40:07,759
我不应该只是 你需要帮助时才来找的女孩
I deserve more than just being the girl that you call when you need something.

527
00:40:08,205 --> 00:40:10,332
你真的以为 可以找到犹他州的钱？
You think you're gonna find the money in Utah?

528
00:40:10,508 --> 00:40:12,999
我不在乎犹他州的钱！
I don't care about the money in Utah.

529
00:40:13,844 --> 00:40:16,506
我不想再犯罪了
I don't want any more crime.

530
00:40:16,680 --> 00:40:21,583
把你们交给警察 我可以拿到二十万，合法的钱
I turn you in, I get $200,000. Legal money.

531
00:40:27,425 --> 00:40:29,154
我要把你们交给警察
You're the policeman's problem now.

532
00:40:29,326 --> 00:40:32,659
-妮卡K -不要靠近我，否则我会开枪
- Nika. - Don't come any closer or I'll shoot you.

533
00:40:33,798 --> 00:40:34,856
你不会开枪的
No, you won't.

534
00:41:04,662 --> 00:41:06,391
祝你好运
Good luck to you.

535
00:41:32,223 --> 00:41:33,884
-你好 -你好
- Hey. - Hey.

536
00:41:34,692 --> 00:41:37,889
总部问你 亚布兹走进房间前
HQ called. They're asking why you didn't intercept Abruzzi...

537
00:41:38,062 --> 00:41:39,859
为何不先拦截他？
...when he was walking towards the motel.

538
00:41:40,631 --> 00:41:43,964
他是个黑帮老大 把他困住是最佳的方式
The man was a mob boss. The right move was to get him trapped.

539
00:41:44,134 --> 00:41:47,433
他们说依照你的方式 只会有一种结果
They're saying the way you played it, there was only one possible outcome.

540
00:41:47,605 --> 00:41:52,235
如果总部对我的方式有意见 欢迎下次拿枪和我一起出勤
HQ has a problem with the way I do it, they can pick a gun and follow me next time.

541
00:41:59,049 --> 00:42:00,038
（黑帮老大亚布兹 被判终身监禁）
Scofield always knew the rat was the key to Abruzzi.

542
00:42:00,217 --> 00:42:02,481
史柯菲知道 叛徒是亚布兹的弱点

543
00:42:02,653 --> 00:42:05,850
我们只是放出诱饵 让亚布兹上勾
We just put it out on the wire and Abruzzi bit.

544
00:42:14,798 --> 00:42:16,197
说到史柯菲
Speaking of scofield...

545
00:42:17,001 --> 00:42:19,162
车子爆炸是假的
...the crash was staged.

546
00:42:25,976 --> 00:42:27,637
是猪血
Pig blood.

547
00:42:29,513 --> 00:42:31,344
聪明的小子
Smart kid.

548
00:42:33,717 --> 00:42:35,048
（奥斯卡席尔斯）

549
00:42:36,587 --> 00:42:40,990
这么聪明 问题就在于迟早K
The problem with being that clever, is that sooner or later...

550
00:42:41,158 --> 00:42:43,422
他会聪明反被聪明误
...you end up getting too clever for your own good.

551
00:42:50,000 --> 00:42:51,399
晚安
Good night.

552
00:43:15,759 --> 00:43:18,728
我一定会让你吃尽苦头
You have no idea what you're in for.

